  in the spec requires: run header, cost, coverage totals, top-5 findings
  by severity, diff-from-last-green block, and a link to report.html.

  Template invariants:
    - Renders to <= 50 lines on the typical green/red case (AC12 expects
      "forwardable as-is" without scroll fatigue).
    - No raw HTML — Markdown only, so the message reads cleanly in
      plain-text email and Slack as well as in any Markdown renderer.
    - All cell values are HTML-escape-safe even though we're in Markdown,
      because the renderer constructs the env with autoescape on for the
      .j2 extension. Backticks around code-ish values keep formatting
      stable in renderers that auto-link bare URLs.
